race.comment: Tricky race. ALGADON STORM (8) resumes having debuted in a rich race at Bendigo, sent around a $5.50 chance on that occasion when not beaten far after settling back in the field. She sets up well here from the gate and the Laurie yard should have her ready. BAJARIA (9) has looked good in two starts to date, boxing on well behind the smart Rohesia in a fast maiden at Geelong last time out. This suits and she has race fitness. CELTICS (4) is a very well bred colt by I Am Invincible on debut for the Price & Kent Jnr yard. He's won a jumpout leading in and represents strong connections. Very wary. HI VAL (11) resumes for her second campaign. Two runs last time in were in good company and she could be an improver this time around I'MATEEZ (6) has good ability and can run well fresh.
